Zarco is a mobile app that aims to link travelers with traveling guides. The app started being developed in October 2015 and had at the time of this interview 8 employees.
In order to manage the workload, the company uses kanban and a white boar.

The team is divided in three modules, on for the iOS app, another for the Android app and another that works with the API.
Internal communication is maintained using both Slack and direct communication.
For version control and code management teams uses Git.
Infrastructure is hosted in a AWS and  it consists in a web server and a bucket used for photos.